      "content": "but \"trying\" feels so exhausting. it's like I'm trying to rebuild a house that's already been burned down to the ground. you say there's always a way out, but what if there isn't? what if some people are just meant to be this way? just... permanently damaged? it feels less like a phase and more like a fact of my existence.",
